==Introduction==
The '''File Type''' represent a file uploaded to the MediaWiki.

The property allows user to enter a name of the file to be displayed.

A file has to be uploaded to the MediaWiki using "Upload file" capability (outside of the form).


==Definition==

The File Property extends a common definition of the [[Help:Property|Property Definition]] with the following elements:

<pre>
<property ... size={SIZE}>
</property>
</pre>

{| class="helptable"
|-
! {SIZE}
| A length of the input field. Default value: 80.
|}


==Semantic database==
The File Property is implemented as a [[Special:Types/Text]] MediaWiki datatype.


==Example==
<pre>
<property name="Filename" type="File" label="File" attribute="filename">
  <description>A filename plus extension of a file - in the file namespace.</description>
  <instruction>A "Filename" is a string value that reflects the name plus extension of a file, as used in the definition of a taxonomy element. This file is typically not an image, for which the Image property is used.</instruction>
</property>
</pre>


==User Interface==
* '''View Page'''
The property displays a link to the file.

* '''Edit Page'''
The property provides one line text input field to enter the file name.
A length of the field is controlled by the 'size' attribute.

* '''Search Page'''
The property allows user to choose a search operator from the following options: ''Starts with, Contains, Equals, Ends with, Has any value''
and allows user to enter a file name in one line text input field.
